48x1365.jpg 2048w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM002-1920x1280.jpg 1920w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM002-480x320.jpg 480w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM002-270x180.jpg 270w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM002-560x373.jpg 560w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" />24 February 2021: Bulawayo started its vaccine rollout with frontline workers, including journalists, at the Northern Suburbs Clinic. Bulawayo is Zimbabwe’s second worst-affected city with 5 281 cases and 203 deaths recorded by 2 March.



Munekayi Padingani, the medical director of Matabeleland North, said he was confident that the programme would reach its target of vaccinating 4 025 people. He attributed the slow start to a lack of awareness among the targeted group.



“As of Wednesday [3 March], we had managed to vaccinate 2 010 people. The campaign has been going well but it started slowly because of a lack of sensitisation. We managed to hold sensitisation meetings in which we did tell people why we are vaccinating, what we are using, who are eligible to get vaccinated, possible side effects and what to do in case such side effects develop,” Padingani said.



Matabeleland South has a target of 5 283 people and nearly half of them had been vaccinated by 3 March.



<img data-attachment-id="122191" data-permalink="https://www.newframe.com/slow-start-to-zimbabwes-vaccination-campaign/8mar_zim-vaccines_km003/" data-orig-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="2560,1707" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;1.7&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;ILCE-7M2&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;24 February 2021: Health workers  at North End Clinic in Bulawayo loading vaccines into a bakkie before proceeding to the next vaccination point.&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1614164729&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;35&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;100&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.0004&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-960x640.jpg" data-large-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-1440x960.jpg" loading="lazy" width="2560" height="1707" src="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-scaled.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-122191" srcset="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-960x640.jpg 960w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-1440x960.jpg 1440w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM003-1920x1280.jpg