Personal experience



The statistics for Bulawayo were not yet available. But the city council’s health department, working in collaboration with the Ministry of Health and Child Care, set aside 2 March as the day on which journalists who wanted it could get the vaccine.



Abigail Khupe, a journalist with a local media house, was among the first media practitioners to be inoculated and said she readily grabbed the chance because she had been ill with Covid-19. 



“Some time last year, I tested positive for Covid-19 and I got quite sick. It was a terrifying experience and I would never want to have it again. I am a mother and I want to protect myself as well as my family from the risk of getting infected, and I believe being vaccinated will help me achieve that.”



<img data-attachment-id="122192" data-permalink="https://www.newframe.com/slow-start-to-zimbabwes-vaccination-campaign/8mar_zim-vaccines_km004/" data-orig-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="2560,1707" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;1.7&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;ILCE-7M2&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;22 February 2021: One of the health workers welcoming people at the ceremony to launch the national vaccine rollout at the United Bulawayo Hospitals.&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1613986646&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;35&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;125&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0.00025&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-960x640.jpg" data-large-file="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-1440x960.jpg" loading="lazy" width="2560" height="1707" src="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-scaled.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-122192" srcset="https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-960x640.jpg 960w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-1440x960.jpg 1440w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-1920x1280.jpg 1920w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-480x320.jpg 480w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-270x180.jpg 270w, https://www.newframe.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/8Mar_Zim-Vaccines_KM004-560x373.jpg 560w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" />22 February 2021: One of the health workers welcoming people at the launch of the national vaccine rollout at United Bulawayo Hospitals.



Journalist Tanaka Gumbo was also inoculated. She said though it was understandable that many people were sceptical about the vaccine, she believed it was safe.



“Whenever there is something new, be it a disease, as is the case with Covid-19, an invention or anything along those lines, there will always be divergent views. But we must bear in mind that Covid-19 has been a devastating pandemic and as such the vaccines have been made as an emergency. There are scientists and medical practitioners who have worked on coming up with these vaccines. They are knowledgeable people and I don’t believe that they would deliberately come up with something that would harm or destroy the whole of humanity,” Gumbo said.



